In your terminal do the following actions

Clone repo by running
```git clone https://github.com/dianagsgs/node-docker.git```

Install all dependencies by running
```npm install```

Setup the database by running
```node db.js```

Create docker image by running
```docker build --tag node-docker .```

Run containerized application by running
```docker run node-docker save [animal] [num_pics]```
or
```docker run node-docker load```

Where the "load" command loads the URL of the last image stored (if any),
while the "save" command saves the specified number of animal pictures for
the animal selected. Note that:
- [animal] can be any of "cat", "dog", or "duck"
- [num_pics] can be any integer between 1 and 20
